too much for one person

01:29:01.803 --> 01:29:04.567
and that it's not fair
to everybody

01:29:04.606 --> 01:29:07.871
because everybody
deserves a chance.

01:29:10.078 --> 01:29:12.046
And...

01:29:14.349 --> 01:29:16.408
And we should change it.

01:29:16.451 --> 01:29:18.078
Objection!

01:29:18.119 --> 01:29:19.780
This isn't a courtroom, Marion.

01:29:21.356 --> 01:29:24.519
I like that idea, Harriet.

01:29:24.559 --> 01:29:26.288
Let's see what the class thinks.

01:29:26.327 --> 01:29:27.919
Miss Elson, I think

01:29:27.996 --> 01:29:30.294
I speak for everyone when I say

01:29:30.331 --> 01:29:34.028
this is, this is a really,
really stupid idea.

01:29:34.068 --> 01:29:35.695
That is one opinion.

01:29:37.238 --> 01:29:39.331
But let's take a vote.

01:29:39.374 --> 01:29:43.538
Marion is now editor
of the Guidepost.

01:29:43.578 --> 01:29:47.412
Would anyone like to nominate
another candidate?

01:29:54.489 --> 01:29:59.392
Well, I guess if no one
has anything to say...

01:30:01.329 --> 01:30:03.854
I have something to say.

01:30:10.238 --> 01:30:15.232
I think that Harriet's
a very good writer and...

01:30:15.276 --> 01:30:18.803
if we only listen
to one person's opinion

01:30:18.846 --> 01:30:21.542
we may never
get anywhere new.

01:30:21.582 --> 01:30:25.416
But Harriet might have
something very original

01:30:25.453 --> 01:30:28.251
and I'd like to read
what she has to write.

01:30:33.428 --> 01:30:36.295
Is there a second?

01:30:36.331 --> 01:30:38.765
I second it.

01:30:44.238 --> 01:30:46.297
I third it.

01:30:50.144 --> 01:30:51.475
Okay, then.

01:30:51.512 --> 01:30:55.346
Harriet Welsch is now
a candidate for editor.

01:30:56.884 --> 01:30:58.511
