Okay, here goes:

01:32:10.825 --> 01:32:13.760
I knew this guy once.

01:32:13.795 --> 01:32:15.956
He used to be a bajillionaire.

01:32:15.997 --> 01:32:18.056
Now he rides a bike.

01:32:18.099 --> 01:32:20.727
Want to know the freaky part?

01:32:23.037 --> 01:32:25.403
He says the bike's better.

01:32:25.440 --> 01:32:28.000
Please write in
if you think he's lying.

01:32:33.147 --> 01:32:37.106
There's a difference
between looking at stuff

01:32:37.151 --> 01:32:39.449
and really seeing it.

01:32:41.456 --> 01:32:43.083
Look who's here.

01:32:43.124 --> 01:32:44.751
Give them some bread, huh?

01:32:44.792 --> 01:32:46.623
Here you are.

01:32:46.661 --> 01:32:48.993
To really see,

01:32:49.063 --> 01:32:51.554
you've got to get a closer look.

01:32:52.633 --> 01:32:53.657
Why, thank you.

01:32:53.701 --> 01:32:54.668
So much.

01:32:54.702 --> 01:32:55.930
A cabbage.

01:32:55.970 --> 01:32:58.734
Carrots in here for you.

01:32:58.773 --> 01:33:00.263
And a sausage.

01:33:14.989 --> 01:33:16.957
I've noticed that, sometimes,

01:33:16.991 --> 01:33:19.926
stuff you think
is broken forever

01:33:19.961 --> 01:33:23.397
is actually totally fixable.

01:33:25.433 --> 01:33:29.767
But some stuff is supposed
to fall apart.

